race.comment: TOMMY STAR (5) has been thereabouts in both of his starts to date. He is a lightly tried 6-year-old gelding who will improve as he gets out over more ground. Include in all combinations. SHES WONDERING (9) has needed plenty of time to mature, and resumes from a spell with a couple of decent trials under her belt. She has also copped a wide gate, but she has to be respected in this sort of field. SUNNY (7) makes his debut and will have Jonathan Riddell in the saddle, which is a good lead. Include in all combinations. MANORBIER (2) was runner-up when resuming at Taupo, and then his next 2 starts in a clockwise direction have not been so good. He can make amends with a return to racing in this direction. Each way value. SUBTLE TIME (16) has been disappointing, but gets another chance in a modest field like this one.
